Introduction

+(KR)ystal Eyes, also known as tripleS KRE, was the second sub-unit of the girl group tripleS under MODHAUS.

On September 16, 2022, MODHAUS announced their First Gravity, titled "Grand Gravity", where fans would be able to vote, using the Cosmo App, to place the eight revealed members in two units of four: Acid Angel from Asia and +(KR)rystal Eyes. SeoYeon was the first member announced on September 22, followed by SooMin on September 23, ChaeYeon on September 24, and JiWoo on September 25.

+(KR)ystal Eyes debuted on May 4, 2023, with the mini album "AESTHETIC". On June 27, 2023, they released the digital single "Touch+", featuring tripleS member SoHyun.
